            c1_bio: "Dr. Viktoriia von Rosen is a financial scientist with many years of experience in academia, banking, and international consulting. She is an active bridge-builder between Ukraine and Germany. Chairwoman of the Board of the Ukrainian Coordination Center e.V., Vice President of the German-Ukrainian Society for Economics and Science.",
            c2_bio: "Sofia Petroshenko is committed to promoting the goals of List 9 and working for integration and equality in Frankfurt.", c3_bio: "Yana Klyzhenko is a psychologist by training, a practicing psychologist, and a trainer. Since March 2022, she has been an active volunteer at the Ukrainian Coordination Center in Frankfurt am Main. She oversees projects supporting Ukraine and the Ukrainian community in Germany, including information and counseling services for refugees, support for families with children with special needs, and the co-organization of cultural events to promote Ukrainian culture and strengthen German-Ukrainian dialogue.", c4_bio: "Iryna Parukh is the deputy head of the Saturday school 'Sun in the Hands' and an expert on housing issues and support for internally displaced persons. She organizes charity and solidarity actions in Germany to support Ukraine and is an active volunteer in the Ukrainian scout organization 'Plast'. Her work focuses on the integration of Ukrainian children in Germany and the promotion of Ukrainian language and culture.",
            c5_bio: "Alina Kerste-Gavriluk is a real estate and housing management professional (IHK), entrepreneur, and managing partner with extensive national and international experience in the real estate and hotel industry. Member of DEHOGA Hessen and the Frankfurt Hotel Alliance e.V. A German citizen living in Germany since 1992. Long-standing, dedicated supporter of the Ukrainian diaspora in Frankfurt am Main. Member of the Ukrainian Coordination Center e.V.",
            c6_bio: "Denis Grinberg was born in Zhytomyr and has lived in Frankfurt since 1997. He is an energy engineer fluent in Ukrainian and German. He is a well-known figure in the Ukrainian volunteer community in Germany, founder of the movement of Ukrainian football fans in Europe, and organizer of numerous sports events over the past 20 years. Co-founder of the Ukrainian Coordination Center e.V. and Inpact e.V. Since 2022, he has been consulting and supporting Ukrainians with temporary protection, helping hundreds of families.",
            c7_bio: "Olena Zhmur is committed to promoting the goals of List 9 and working for integration and equality in Frankfurt.",
            c8_bio: "Lali Davitidze is an economist by education and a successful entrepreneur with 25 years of experience. Her active civic and personal position laid the foundation for her participation in the development of the Ukrainian Coordination Center in Frankfurt since March 2022. Her ability to identify urgent issues, clearly define them, and initiate solutions allows her to actively implement full-cycle projects to support Ukraine and Ukrainians in Frankfurt‚Äîfrom idea to realization. Her successful integration into the German labor market and the consistent implementation of her own professional projects enable her to understand the real challenges of today.",
            c9_bio: "Nataliia Pokhylko is a cultural figure and director of the vocal studio 'Ukrainian Pearls'. She is dedicated to developing cultural dialogue between Ukraine and Germany, fostering intercultural cooperation, social integration, and strengthening bilateral cultural ties.",
            c10_bio: "Iryna Manoilova. Since March 2022, she has been volunteering with a focus on fostering social and cultural ties between Germany and Ukraine. Her work includes coordinating collaborations with museums and exhibition centers, as well as organizing workshops and leisure activities for Ukrainian children. Before 2022, she served as a Head of Procurement for twelve years. She holds two university degrees: one in Electronic Engineering and one in Finance.",
            c11_bio: "Svitlana Prokopenko is a lawyer specializing in international and European law and holds two LL.M. degrees from Ukraine and Lithuania. She worked at the Constitutional Court of Ukraine. After the full-scale invasion, she continued her career in Germany, including in banking supervision at the ECB. Today, she works in non-financial risk management at a European financial institution and is actively involved as a volunteer representing the voice of Ukraine in public initiatives.",
            c12_bio: "Dr. Olga Biegunova is a mathematician by training and came to Germany as an IT specialist in 2001. Since then, she has been working professionally in IT and earned her doctorate in 2009 from the University of Bielefeld. Since 2014, she has been actively involved in supporting Ukraine, first in the OBOZ association and later with Prostir Zbirka, where she organizes cultural events with like-minded people and continues to collect humanitarian aid for Ukraine. She volunteers as a youth leader in the PLAST Ukrainian Scout Association in Germany.",
            c13_bio: "Iryna Kaplonova has many years of experience in sales, tourism, and network marketing. She is a wellness consultant and a volunteer at the Ukrainian Coordination Center e.V., dedicated to uniting Ukrainians around Ukrainian musical culture and promoting it in Germany. She is the organizer and a singer of the Ukrainian choir 'ORANTA', which aims to build intercultural connections with musical associations in Germany and practice cultural diplomacy.",
            c14_bio: "Yelyzaveta (Liza) Werner is an experienced freelance graphic designer with a focus on web and urban design. In Frankfurt, she is an active part of the local international creative community. Liza fosters multicultural identity through her passion for traditional Ukrainian arts and crafts. She is a regular member and a volunteer of the Ukrainian Coordination Center e.V. and is responsible for the visual communication, promoting dialogue and media production. Liza‚Äôs goal is to support Ukrainians integrate into Frankfurt, the heart of Europe.",
            c15_bio: "Olena Levchenko is committed to promoting the goals of List 9 and working for integration and equality in Frankfurt.",
